        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 10 at 9:47PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 947 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Bevill Lock And Dam to
Macon to near Mashulaville. Movement was southeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Aliceville, Snoddy, New Mount Hebron, Panola, George Downer Airport,
West Greene, Union, Pleasant Ridge, Lewiston, Benevola, Johnston
Lake, Memphis, Bevill Lock And Dam, Gainesville Lake Campground,
Garden, Geiger, Warsaw, New West Greene, Mantua, and Pickensville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1100 PM CDT for
west central Alabama.</instruction>
